Thamnocephalidae is a family of crustaceans with wide distribution including Western Australia and Southern Africa. It was originally described as a subfamily of Branchipodidae by Alpheus Spring Packard in 1883, and elevated to the rank of family by Simon in 1886. Six genera are recognised, in two subfamilies:
ThamnocephalinaeThamnocephalus Packard, 1879
Carinophallus Rogers, 2006BranchinellinaeDendrocephalus Daday, 1908
